'''Golden Arm''' is a term used for a [[craps]] player who has rolled [[dice]] for over one hour without losing.<ref name=":1">{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-vegas-golden-arms-20170429-story.html|title=A method to their magic: Craps champions swear it’s more mystique than math at the tables in Vegas|first=David|last=Montero|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/93155586-132.html|title=The Golden Arms of craps|first=Los Angeles|last=Times|website=latimes.com}}</ref> The designation was created by the [[California Hotel and Casino]] in 1989 after Stanley Fujitake rolled for three hours and six minutes (without losing).<ref name=":1"/><ref name=":2"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lasvegassun.com/news/2000/may/03/welcome-to-the-golden-arm-club-where-membership-is/|title=Welcome to the Golden Arm Club, where membership is earned by hour-plus dice-throwing|date=3 May 2000|publisher=}}</ref>

