{{About|Theater operations|Household servants|Butler}}
{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
In [[theatre]], '''house management''' concerns the selling of [[Ticket (admission)|ticket]]s, the [[wiktionary:usher|usher]]ing of [[patron]]s in [[FOH (theatre)|front of house]] areas, and the maintenance and management of the [[Theater (structure)|theatre building]]. House management staff usually work for the theatre, under the supervision of the ''house manager'', and not for the theatrical [[wiktionary:troupe|troupe]] which is occupying it. Often in regional or smaller theatres the responsibility falls under the aegis of the ''production manager''. In any case, house management works closely with the [[production management]] team for the presentation of the theatrical production.

In domestic services, "house management" refers to the overseeing of employees that make up the staff of the household, including drivers, nannies, and housekeepers.

