{{Infobox company |name = Praesepe |logo = |type = |foundation = 2007 |location_city =[[Milton Keynes]] |location_country = UK |location = |locations = |key_people = |area_served = |industry = [[Gambling]] |products = |services = |operating_income = |revenue = |net_income = |num_employees = |parent = [[Gauselmann]] |subsid = [[Cashino]] |slogan = |homepage = |dissolved = |footnotes = |intl = }}
'''Praesepe ''' is a British bingo, arcade gaming and gambling company formed in 2007 based in [[Milton Keynes]]. It owns the high street gambling arcade chain [[Cashino]].
Praesepe was founded in October 2007 by Nick Harding and the private equity firm [[Marwyn Partners]].<ref name=Praesepe>{{cite web|title=About Us|url=http://praesepeplc.com/history-of-the-company/|website=Praesepe|accessdate=22 April 2015}}</ref>
In autumn 2012, Praesepe became a subsidiary of [[Gauselmann]], the German gaming and gambling company founded by [[Paul Gauselmann]].<ref name=Praesepe />
